Google is increasing the price of YouTube TV for new customers to $40 per month, the company announced. Customers who are signed up before 13 March will keep the original price of $35 per month. The price increase will coincide with subscribers receiving access to several additional TV networks, including TNT, Adult Swim, TBS, and CNN. Google said users will also have access to “March Madness” and can watch televised NBA games, NBA All-Star weekend, NBA Playoff games, MLB Postseason games, the PGA Championship, and the UEFA Champions League.